    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-28T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-28T20:00:00-05:00" n="474"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d474">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.504 Mexico/14: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Messersmith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-28T19:00:00-06:00"
                            >July 28, 1943—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 30—12:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>754. Reference Embassy despatch No. 11, 116 of June 30.<note n="44"
                        xml:id="d474fn44">Not printed.</note> Brown of FSA saw Padilla Nervo this
                    afternoon and received virtual ultimatum from him that all recruiting of labor
                    must stop unless suggested arrangements for Mexican labor inspectors are
                    approved not later than July 31. Brown has wired San Francisco and Hough<note
                        n="45" xml:id="d474fn45">Samuel Hough, Representative of the War Manpower
                        Commission.</note> has telephoned Washington. He hopes you can get in touch
                    with Colonel Bruton<note n="46" xml:id="d474fn46">Col. Philip G. Bruton, Deputy
                        War Food Administrator.</note> to expedite decision.</p>
                <p>Brown says even brief delay in recruiting will jeopardize August schedule.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Messersmith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
